document.title: samba bug fix and enhancement update

notes.text:
An update is available for samba.
This update affects Rocky Linux 8 from CIQ.
A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
For detailed information on changes in this release, see the Rocky Enterprise Software Foundation
Enterprise Linux 8.5 Release Notes linked from the References section.

This advisory is provided by CIQ Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.
notes.title: Description

remediations.details:
Apply the security update for CRLBA-2021:4438 by updating the affected packages using your Rocky Linux from CIQ package manager.

For Rocky Linux from CIQ systems, run:
sudo dnf update

Or update specific packages:
sudo dnf update ctdb libsmbclient libsmbclient-devel libwbclient libwbclient-devel python3-samba python3-samba-test samba samba-client samba-client-libs samba-common samba-common-libs samba-common-tools samba-devel samba-krb5-printing samba-libs samba-pidl samba-test samba-test-libs samba-vfs-iouring samba-winbind samba-winbind-clients samba-winbind-krb5-locator samba-winbind-modules samba-winexe

After updating, verify the installed package versions are greater thanor equal to those specified in this advisory.
